™’Ł@2f3d4308ee04d05432c6ab24c86fa0061c32f8d9ba710fa57937e57caa68d64bŚØTitle: title: Nushell 0.27
Path: Nushell 0.27
Content:




Nushell, or Nu for short, is a new shell that takes a modern, structured approach to your commandline. It works seamlessly with the data from your filesystem, operating system, and a growing number of file formats to make it easy to build powerful commandline pipelines.
Today, we're releasing 0.27 of Nu. This release fixes some long-standing issues with Nushell.
’Ł@8b89d77746c5ac96a07c7ba58b1e3e87b420123750fcf4f779e918a433448de4ŚTitle: title: Nushell 0.27
Path: Where to get it
Content:
Nu 0.27 is available as 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/releases/tag/0.27.0] pre-built binaries
 or from 
[link: https://crates.io/crates/nu] crates.io
. If you have Rust installed you can install it using 
``cargo install nu``
.
If you want all the goodies, you can install 
``cargo install nu --features=extra``
.
As part of this release, we also publish a set of plugins you can install and use with Nu. To install, use 
``cargo install nu_plugin_<plugin name>``
.
’Ł@2deb280769ac1a73d9c21042ffe17c900ffe956b7bf3a35fc485b2adb94f0ebeŚ$Title: title: Nushell 0.27
Path: Book updates (fdncred, sophiajt)
Content:
The Nushell book received some much-needed updates. You'll notice new chapters and updated chapters to bring it more up-to-date with recent Nushell.
[link: https://www.nushell.sh/book/configuration.html] Thoroughly updated configuration section
[link: https://www.nushell.sh/book/types_of_data.html] Updated section on data types
[link: https://www.nushell.sh/book/custom_commands.html] A new section on creating your own commands
[link: https://www.nushell.sh/book/aliases.html] An updated section on aliases
[link: https://www.nushell.sh/book/variables.html] A new section on working with variables and expressions
[link: https://www.nushell.sh/book/scripts.html] The start of a new section on writing your own Nushell scripts
’Ł@ba38f81160d6536c4343ea810fb69aa4d9f5c5d67e90520331627a3d9be3b3e0ŚdTitle: title: Nushell 0.27
Path: New commands (fdncred)
Content:
A new 
``term size``
 commands 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3038] lets you get the current size of the terminal
New 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2976] ``pow``
 operator
New 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2975] modulus(
``%``
) operator
’Ł@88833ad051bf62af8808d9c2aaee6268a52226e0c006853f53725af5093287ceŚITitle: title: Nushell 0.27
Path: Functionality (sophiajt, WatsonThink, ilius, andrasio, Qwanve, fdncred, ammkrn)
Content:
Tables now 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3061] truncate instead of crashing when too large
``source``
 command now can 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3059] use tilde in the path
``let-env``
 can now shadow 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3057] environment variables
 in addition to adding new ones
Prompts can now call 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3056] external commands on initial startup
You can now configure the 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3045] file size standard to use
Strings can now be passed in where 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3048] column-paths were expected
 and 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3016] here
More 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3035] file size types have been added
``sort-by``
 can now 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3025] reverse sort
``which``
 can now take 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3024] multiple applications
``ps -l``
 now has 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3015] a cleaner output when the parent is missing
``select``
 can no longer 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3012] select the same column twice
``to-md --per-element``
 now gives you 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2997] more fine-grained control over the markdown output
A new 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2995] ``$nothing``
 built-in variable to help check for the existence of a value
``str from``
 can convert 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2977] more things to strings
Booleans are now shown as 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3043] true/false instead of Yes/No
’Ł@c791af333e790c968d102b6082de895a7e0098b7a6a59e8426fb1488aa151ef2Ś‰Title: title: Nushell 0.27
Path: Internal (stormasm, ilius, fdncred, LhKipp, RReverser, sophiajt)
Content:
Some 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3053] comment parsing improvements
The 
``block``
 function is now 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3047] ``parse_block``
More 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/3000] Value helpers were added
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2986] Parser cleanup for handling 
``def``
The 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2983] WASI build should now be working again
File size is 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/2984] now a big int
’Ł@d8f5efc4014cc6ba53dd3cbafed232da18468e1b43d3a7765905d36c2db4b8bbŚDTitle: title: Nushell 0.27
